HEADWORD: Stockfish
<hw>Stock"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>stokvisch</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Salted and dried fish,
especially codfish, hake, ling, and torsk; also, codfish dried without
being salted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Young fresh cod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stockholder</ent>⟦br⟧
